                            <comment id="59832" author="pjones" created="Sat, 1 Jun 2013 00:53:24 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That&apos;s great Kevin. It&apos;s clearly important to get this stuff right for the next round of releases. The 2.4.0 release is already completed, but I will personally take ownership of this ticket and make any needed changes ahead of the 2.5 release. See you in Chicago!&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="59705" author="kevcanady" created="Thu, 30 May 2013 22:36:59 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Peter, for keeping an eye on this.  I have escalated this as well on my side to provide further guidance.  Regards, Kevin&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="59686" author="pjones" created="Thu, 30 May 2013 19:28:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Kevin&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks for this information. I appreciate that you will not be able to read the internal link Dan mentions above, but the gist of it is that Intel has a standard practice relating to third party trademarks which is what we have been adhering to. However, I have forwarded the Xyratex package to our legal department soon and am awaiting guidance&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Regards&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="59685" author="kevcanady" created="Thu, 30 May 2013 19:23:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Dan, Please send a working link.  We will need to review as Lustre name is not an Intel property in which it can regulate how to properly note it&apos;s registration.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks,&lt;br/&gt;
Kevin&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="59599" author="adilger" created="Thu, 30 May 2013 03:32:06 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I removed the already-released versions, since they can&apos;t be retro-actively updated.  This only affects new releases.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="59596" author="green" created="Thu, 30 May 2013 02:03:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I assume you guys have a patch ready? Can you please include a pointer to it?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
